description:
Dark times are here, and even darker times are coming. What can we do to pierce the darkness? There is only one answer – seek the One who is the light – Jesus! Jesus is the light of the world, and He looks to His people to reflect His light as they behold Him.  Are you reflecting His light?

“Arise, shine; For your light has come! And the glory of the Lord is risen upon you. For behold, the darkness shall cover the earth, And deep darkness the people; But the Lord will arise over you, And His glory will be seen upon you. The Gentiles shall come to your light, And kings to the brightness of your rising (Isaiah 60:1-3).”

This #short clip from the Global #Campmeeting sermon, “The Mission and Focus of the Remnant” https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JC1Vwnnbads&list=PL-k2Gb-DBYo9tb9fHW_AxGxJ1R8MpNnpa&index=2  with Pastor Ryan Day explains our role in piercing the darkness and letting God’s light shine through. 

Watch the video to realize how reflecting His light is the most important part of our mission.
